WEBVTT

00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:55.400


00:00:58.364 --> 00:01:02.912
[Episode 7: Low-Power Mode Human]

00:01:43.730 --> 00:01:46.820
- Spin it, spin it!
- Come on, faster!

00:01:46.820 --> 00:01:50.397
People fall into two types.

00:01:50.397 --> 00:01:55.185
Some get energized being around people...

00:01:55.185 --> 00:01:58.855
Others get totally drained in crowds.

00:01:58.855 --> 00:02:00.482
That's me.

00:02:00.482 --> 00:02:03.485
See? Told you he could do it.

00:02:03.485 --> 00:02:05.590
Did you see his speed?

00:02:05.590 --> 00:02:06.863
Yeah, I saw it.

00:02:06.863 --> 00:02:08.807
- Pretty insane, right?
- Seriously.

00:02:08.807 --> 00:02:11.318
That was incredible.

00:02:12.218 --> 00:02:14.437
Let's get a hit!

00:02:16.039 --> 00:02:17.708
- Get up, PD Shin.
- No, I'm good.

00:02:17.708 --> 00:02:19.001
Come on, get up. Join us.

00:02:19.001 --> 00:02:21.461
Let me hear you!

00:02:21.461 --> 00:02:23.864
♪ Get a hit, come on ♪

00:02:23.864 --> 00:02:26.550
♪ Get a hit ♪
Go, go!

00:02:26.550 --> 00:02:28.176
♪ We want a home run ♪

00:02:28.176 --> 00:02:31.179
How?
♪ Knock it out of the park ♪

00:02:31.179 --> 00:02:32.973
♪ Send it flying ♪
Get a hit!

00:02:32.973 --> 00:02:35.601
♪ Get a hit, come on ♪

00:02:35.601 --> 00:02:38.145
♪ Get a hit ♪

00:02:38.145 --> 00:02:40.480
♪ We want a home run ♪
Sorry, my boss is calling.

00:02:40.480 --> 00:02:42.899
How?
♪ Knock it out of the park ♪

00:02:42.899 --> 00:02:47.403
♪ Send it flying, right now ♪

00:02:51.491 --> 00:02:53.647
Okay, got it.

00:02:53.647 --> 00:02:56.705
I'll double-check and send it over.

00:02:56.705 --> 00:02:58.424
Okay.

00:03:03.295 --> 00:03:06.340
If I weren't managing a writer
who writes baseball novels,

00:03:06.340 --> 00:03:09.058
I'd never be somewhere like this.

00:03:28.070 --> 00:03:30.555
To conserve energy,

00:03:30.555 --> 00:03:33.982
I stay in low-power mode outside.

00:03:38.622 --> 00:03:40.540
So during the day,

00:03:40.540 --> 00:03:43.968
only Rational Cell is active.

00:03:45.438 --> 00:03:47.005
Look at that.

00:03:47.005 --> 00:03:49.675
When did all those flowers bloom?

00:03:49.675 --> 00:03:50.717
Yeah.

00:03:50.717 --> 00:03:53.720
The weather's so nice today.

00:03:53.720 --> 00:03:55.681
I want to go out.

00:03:55.681 --> 00:03:57.557
Same here.

00:03:57.557 --> 00:03:59.918
Should we just ditch work right now?

00:03:59.918 --> 00:04:02.208
- Really?
- Really?

00:04:03.467 --> 00:04:06.522
No way. Absolutely not.

00:04:07.248 --> 00:04:09.133
Too bad.

00:04:17.691 --> 00:04:20.588
The Rational Cell doesn't get caught up
in pointless emotions.

00:04:20.588 --> 00:04:22.582
That's why it works fast.

00:04:22.582 --> 00:04:24.167
Plus...

00:04:24.167 --> 00:04:26.127
Would you like something to drink?

00:04:26.127 --> 00:04:28.679
No, I'm good.

00:04:30.048 --> 00:04:32.397
Oh, I have some chocolates I got as a gift...

00:04:32.397 --> 00:04:33.968
Then...

00:04:33.968 --> 00:04:36.980
I should get going.

00:04:36.980 --> 00:04:38.039
Okay.

00:04:38.039 --> 00:04:40.342
I'm good at saying no, too.

00:04:45.580 --> 00:04:48.421
Keeping clear boundaries
also helps me save energy.

00:04:48.421 --> 00:04:51.341
You're really calm and rational.

00:04:51.341 --> 00:04:53.203
Nice.

00:04:58.688 --> 00:05:00.019
Calm and rational.

00:05:00.019 --> 00:05:03.446
That's how people see Soon Rok.

00:05:05.500 --> 00:05:08.834
Strike three!

00:05:08.834 --> 00:05:10.647
- Strike three!
- Editor.

00:05:10.647 --> 00:05:12.215
Here, sir.

00:05:12.215 --> 00:05:15.176
Strike three!

00:05:15.176 --> 00:05:17.088
Strike three!

00:05:17.088 --> 00:05:18.596
Strike three!

00:05:18.596 --> 00:05:20.197
Come on, do better than that.

00:05:20.197 --> 00:05:21.808
Strike three!

00:05:21.808 --> 00:05:23.710
The only downside is,

00:05:23.710 --> 00:05:25.052
when he's outside,

00:05:25.052 --> 00:05:28.896
none of his other cells are active.

00:05:30.355 --> 00:05:31.765
Let's dig in.

00:05:31.765 --> 00:05:34.194
Oh, thanks.

00:05:34.194 --> 00:05:36.605
That marinated crab looks incredible.

00:05:36.605 --> 00:05:38.281
- I'm already drooling.
- Eat up.

00:05:38.281 --> 00:05:40.980
Not my treat though.

00:05:40.980 --> 00:05:43.201
Enjoy. Food's all that matters anyway.

00:05:43.201 --> 00:05:44.992
What else is there in life?

00:05:46.331 --> 00:05:48.725
I don't even register what I'm eating.

00:05:48.725 --> 00:05:51.669
Hey, "Attack of the Bats" just came out.

00:05:51.669 --> 00:05:52.897
Who's in after this?

00:05:52.897 --> 00:05:54.797
- Me! I've been wanting to see it!
- Of course.

00:05:54.797 --> 00:05:57.733
Let's go, go!

00:05:57.733 --> 00:05:59.844
Sorry, but I...

00:05:59.844 --> 00:06:02.313
You're coming, right, PD Shin?

00:06:02.313 --> 00:06:04.558
If you're not going, I'm not going either.

00:06:04.558 --> 00:06:05.600
I mean it.

00:06:05.600 --> 00:06:07.435
- Come on, PD Shin.
- Come on.

00:06:07.435 --> 00:06:08.647
I'm not going either.

00:06:08.647 --> 00:06:10.188
- Come with us.
- PD Shin!

00:06:10.188 --> 00:06:12.815
- You have to come.
- PD Shin!

00:06:12.815 --> 00:06:15.409
PD Shin!

00:06:40.218 --> 00:06:42.895
He's spilling the popcorn.

00:07:04.966 --> 00:07:08.403
Who checks their phone in a theater?

00:07:16.520 --> 00:07:20.049
I can't even focus on the movie.

00:07:20.049 --> 00:07:21.951
Isn't it getting pretty late?

00:07:21.951 --> 00:07:23.720
There it is.

00:07:23.720 --> 00:07:26.438
The movie was longer than expected.

00:07:27.407 --> 00:07:28.680
I'll get going.

00:07:28.680 --> 00:07:29.738
Bye.

00:07:29.738 --> 00:07:31.313
Get home safe.

00:07:31.313 --> 00:07:34.113
Don't say you were with us.

00:07:41.870 --> 00:07:43.114
Hello.

00:07:43.114 --> 00:07:47.054
On top of that, I'm running out of time.

00:07:50.368 --> 00:07:53.181
The door's closing.

00:08:00.587 --> 00:08:02.013
Hello.

00:08:02.013 --> 00:08:03.426
I'm still not comfortable with this team.

00:08:03.426 --> 00:08:05.539
Sorry, I'm a bit late...

00:08:05.539 --> 00:08:09.332
And now there's even a dog.

00:08:13.186 --> 00:08:15.188
PD Shin,

00:08:15.188 --> 00:08:17.865
do you have anything to say?

00:08:26.295 --> 00:08:27.742
Gosh.

00:08:27.742 --> 00:08:30.822
I can't focus on the script.

00:08:31.704 --> 00:08:33.790
"How can someone in love"

00:08:33.790 --> 00:08:36.467
"possibly stay calm?"

00:08:40.438 --> 00:08:42.382
Sorry, what does that even mean?

00:08:42.382 --> 00:08:46.643
"How can someone in love possibly stay calm?"

00:08:47.845 --> 00:08:51.130
What does love have to do with being calm?

00:09:00.065 --> 00:09:01.272
A Maltese.

00:09:01.272 --> 00:09:03.592
Yeah, let's just talk about the Maltese.

00:09:03.592 --> 00:09:06.781
No need to overthink that one.

00:09:06.781 --> 00:09:08.487
But Maltese dogs

00:09:08.487 --> 00:09:10.410
aren't that smart.

00:09:10.410 --> 00:09:12.053
They're not?

00:09:12.053 --> 00:09:13.355
I thought they were.

00:09:13.355 --> 00:09:15.106
Not particularly.

00:09:15.106 --> 00:09:16.749
That's it.

00:09:16.749 --> 00:09:18.401
Nice save, Soon Rok.

00:09:18.401 --> 00:09:21.620
Let's dodge the situation with the Maltese.

00:09:23.481 --> 00:09:26.783
When I'm in a bad mood,
she stays quiet beside me...

00:09:29.585 --> 00:09:31.139
She's actually really smart.

00:09:31.139 --> 00:09:33.444
Don't all dogs do that?

00:09:33.444 --> 00:09:35.605
Unless it's a lizard.

00:09:35.605 --> 00:09:36.813
Right.

00:09:36.813 --> 00:09:40.967
Dogs and lizards.
That's an interesting comparison.

00:09:51.701 --> 00:09:53.394
Going down.

00:09:53.394 --> 00:09:54.572
Good work today.

00:09:54.572 --> 00:09:55.693
Good work.

00:09:55.693 --> 00:09:58.284
Hang in there.

00:09:58.284 --> 00:10:00.193
- Bye, Coco.
- Take care.

00:10:00.193 --> 00:10:02.620
The door's closing.

00:10:07.062 --> 00:10:08.147
But...

00:10:08.147 --> 00:10:10.438
Writer Kim should be a little upset.

00:10:10.438 --> 00:10:11.497
Why?

00:10:11.497 --> 00:10:14.429
You know, PD Shin said
Maltese dogs aren't that smart.

00:10:14.429 --> 00:10:16.216
Yeah, she didn't seem too happy.

00:10:16.216 --> 00:10:18.018
I wasn't talking about her.

00:10:18.018 --> 00:10:20.587
I said the Maltese wasn't smart.
Why would she be upset?

00:10:20.587 --> 00:10:22.355
Still, from her perspective...

00:10:22.355 --> 00:10:24.293
It's not even her dog.

00:10:24.293 --> 00:10:27.461
Even so, it just feels...

00:10:27.461 --> 00:10:29.321
Oh my, you're so cold.

00:10:29.321 --> 00:10:31.622
Way too rational.

00:10:34.326 --> 00:10:35.994
What are they talking about?

00:10:35.994 --> 00:10:38.747
Writer Kim isn't a Maltese,

00:10:38.747 --> 00:10:40.778
and she's not even the owner.

00:10:40.778 --> 00:10:44.151
So why would she be upset?

00:10:45.879 --> 00:10:48.948
I don't know.

00:11:07.772 --> 00:11:11.655
Today was too much.

00:11:11.655 --> 00:11:15.865
I carried the whole day on my own.

00:11:15.865 --> 00:11:18.203
I know.

00:11:18.203 --> 00:11:20.022
But it's okay.

00:11:20.022 --> 00:11:22.083
I'm almost home.

00:12:19.555 --> 00:12:21.730
Because I'm...

00:12:23.851 --> 00:12:26.277
a total homebody.

00:12:42.605 --> 00:12:45.581
Going out is exhausting.

00:12:45.581 --> 00:12:48.216
Home is the best.

00:12:54.381 --> 00:12:57.684
When I'm home, all my senses come alive.

00:13:11.065 --> 00:13:12.624
Perfect.

00:13:16.111 --> 00:13:18.163
My sense of taste kicks in,

00:13:20.616 --> 00:13:22.709
and my hearing sharpens,

00:13:38.133 --> 00:13:39.480
That's it!

00:13:39.480 --> 00:13:41.595
Good eye!

00:13:41.595 --> 00:13:43.661
Bases loaded!

00:13:44.348 --> 00:13:46.414
Yes!

00:13:48.313 --> 00:13:50.980
Baseball is best with commentary.

00:14:04.647 --> 00:14:06.698
Is he dead?

00:14:18.923 --> 00:14:21.429
Movies are meant to be watched
from the comfort of home.

00:14:21.429 --> 00:14:23.303
That's the way to do it.

00:14:27.098 --> 00:14:30.168
At home, my emotions peak,

00:14:30.168 --> 00:14:32.404
and I can even pick up
on the writer's hidden intentions

00:14:32.404 --> 00:14:34.480
between the lines.

00:14:34.480 --> 00:14:35.690
Back then...

00:14:35.690 --> 00:14:37.317
Did he leave his phone behind?

00:14:37.317 --> 00:14:39.986
The phone began to ring,

00:14:39.986 --> 00:14:43.656
and Sun Ju's eyes were drawn to it.

00:14:43.656 --> 00:14:46.367
Whose call could it be?

00:14:46.367 --> 00:14:48.494
A name she had forgotten.

00:14:48.494 --> 00:14:50.409
[Yoo Da Eun, Intern]
It was Eun Young.

00:14:51.456 --> 00:14:54.917
In that moment, Sun Ju realized

00:14:54.917 --> 00:14:58.288
just how calm she was.

00:14:58.288 --> 00:15:02.055
[Missed Call]

00:15:28.563 --> 00:15:30.703
How can someone in love

00:15:30.703 --> 00:15:33.587
possibly stay calm?

00:15:43.105 --> 00:15:45.945
It wasn't about the Maltese...

00:15:47.728 --> 00:15:50.264
Writer Kim, this is Shin Soon Rok.

00:15:50.264 --> 00:15:53.263
I've added my feedback and sent it over.

00:16:11.688 --> 00:16:14.345
A homebody's nights are always too short.

00:16:17.855 --> 00:16:20.889
And the worst thing for someone like me is...

00:16:25.986 --> 00:16:27.492
[PD Jang Su Hye]

00:16:28.656 --> 00:16:30.272
- Hello?
- Hey, Soon Rok.

00:16:30.272 --> 00:16:31.973
Sorry, are you home right now?

00:16:31.973 --> 00:16:33.752
Do you have anything going on today?

00:16:33.752 --> 00:16:35.476
No.

00:16:35.476 --> 00:16:37.252
But why...

00:16:40.688 --> 00:16:42.169
Right now?

00:16:43.036 --> 00:16:44.750
A day like this.

00:16:45.821 --> 00:16:48.325
An unplanned... weekend business trip.

00:16:48.325 --> 00:16:50.394
Okay, I understand.

00:16:50.394 --> 00:16:53.672
What the...

00:16:53.672 --> 00:16:56.182
It's Saturday.

00:17:20.635 --> 00:17:24.148
There's no time. Just go.

00:17:41.123 --> 00:17:43.049
Hello.

00:17:54.600 --> 00:17:56.805
[From Seoul to Busan]

00:18:02.134 --> 00:18:04.457
I forgot my glasses.

00:18:04.457 --> 00:18:07.208
You even forgot your glasses?

00:18:10.730 --> 00:18:12.238
Wait, no.

00:18:12.238 --> 00:18:14.569
If I burn out this early,

00:18:14.569 --> 00:18:17.300
how am I supposed to get through today?

00:18:34.186 --> 00:18:35.987
Sorry.

00:19:04.540 --> 00:19:07.460
You're really going to
meet the writer like this?

00:19:07.460 --> 00:19:10.379
You didn't even wash your face.

00:19:10.379 --> 00:19:12.460
What about your image?

00:19:24.651 --> 00:19:25.855
That's good.

00:19:25.855 --> 00:19:28.189
I didn't want to go alone anyway.

00:19:28.189 --> 00:19:30.272
Please, have a seat.

00:19:30.272 --> 00:19:32.109
Sit far away.

00:19:32.109 --> 00:19:33.194
No, it's okay.

00:19:33.194 --> 00:19:35.240
My seat is over there.

00:19:49.460 --> 00:19:52.630
You don't even know the schedule yet.

00:19:52.630 --> 00:19:56.133
You're a mess, and you forgot your glasses.

00:19:56.133 --> 00:19:59.443
Gosh, today is seriously the worst.

00:19:59.443 --> 00:20:02.223
Yes, I received the book talk materials,

00:20:02.223 --> 00:20:06.001
but I don't have the contact info
for the person in charge.

00:20:06.001 --> 00:20:07.980
Yes, thank you.

00:20:07.980 --> 00:20:10.356
Oh, sorry, and also...

00:20:10.356 --> 00:20:11.900
the car...

00:20:11.900 --> 00:20:13.729
Oh, the rental.

00:20:13.729 --> 00:20:15.143
Yes.

00:20:21.202 --> 00:20:23.494
Let me sit here for a moment.

00:20:23.494 --> 00:20:24.620
What?

00:20:24.620 --> 00:20:27.304
What is she saying?

00:20:27.304 --> 00:20:29.333
I need to tell you something.

00:20:29.333 --> 00:20:32.133
Do you not like working with me?

00:20:34.375 --> 00:20:35.950
What?

00:20:38.384 --> 00:20:40.480
What did she just say?

00:20:40.480 --> 00:20:44.140
She asked if he doesn't like working with her?

00:20:44.140 --> 00:20:45.725
I don't know either.

00:20:45.725 --> 00:20:46.980
I'm not sure what she means.

00:20:46.980 --> 00:20:49.103
Could you explain more specifically?

00:20:49.103 --> 00:20:51.270
I think I need to hear this.

00:20:56.025 --> 00:20:58.736
What does she want to hear?

00:20:58.736 --> 00:21:00.447
Specifically?

00:21:00.447 --> 00:21:02.730
What is she talking about?

00:21:02.730 --> 00:21:05.063
Is she mad right now?

00:21:05.063 --> 00:21:06.605
Why is she mad?

00:21:06.605 --> 00:21:09.205
She even brought me a drink earlier.

00:21:09.205 --> 00:21:10.873
What is this all of a sudden?

00:21:10.873 --> 00:21:13.526
No...

00:21:15.002 --> 00:21:16.356
Yeah?

00:21:17.755 --> 00:21:19.507
I'm not sure what you mean...

00:21:19.507 --> 00:21:22.272
I mean I want to know the real reason.

00:21:22.272 --> 00:21:24.414
Why you're leaving our team.

00:21:24.414 --> 00:21:26.855
Didn't the Editor tell you?

00:21:26.855 --> 00:21:28.140
My schedules kept overlapping...

00:21:28.140 --> 00:21:30.121
That's just an excuse.

00:21:30.121 --> 00:21:31.931
An excuse?

00:21:32.772 --> 00:21:33.980
PD Shin.

00:21:33.980 --> 00:21:36.478
I've been patient for a long time.

00:21:36.478 --> 00:21:39.390
I'm not usually someone
who gets this worked up,

00:21:39.390 --> 00:21:42.590
but lately, it's been really frustrating.

00:21:46.548 --> 00:21:47.577
What?

00:21:47.577 --> 00:21:50.323
Something's seriously off here.

00:21:52.164 --> 00:21:54.400
Everyone, wake up!

00:21:54.400 --> 00:21:57.686
This is an emergency!

00:22:01.689 --> 00:22:03.606
No!

00:22:05.261 --> 00:22:06.534
My gosh.

00:22:06.534 --> 00:22:09.890
He's completely drained.

00:22:09.890 --> 00:22:11.700
PD Shin?

00:22:35.813 --> 00:22:39.008
[Episode 8: Out of the Blue]

00:22:50.723 --> 00:22:52.516
PD Shin?

00:23:10.424 --> 00:23:11.994
Is he smiling?

00:23:11.994 --> 00:23:14.163
He's smiling right now?

00:23:14.163 --> 00:23:15.188
Why is he smiling?

00:23:15.188 --> 00:23:16.546
Yumi's serious now.

00:23:16.546 --> 00:23:17.750
Are you kidding?

00:23:17.750 --> 00:23:20.810
You should answer her.
What the hell are you laughing for?

00:23:24.230 --> 00:23:27.551
Yumi just laid everything out there,

00:23:29.151 --> 00:23:32.633
so why aren't you saying anything? You punk!

00:23:33.930 --> 00:23:37.452
What was that? There weren't even any clouds.

00:24:00.557 --> 00:24:02.231
Hey...

00:24:03.220 --> 00:24:04.371
PD Shin,

00:24:04.371 --> 00:24:06.923
why were you smiling...

00:24:08.239 --> 00:24:09.953
[PD Jang Su Hye]

00:24:11.762 --> 00:24:14.912
Sorry, this is an urgent call.

00:24:18.978 --> 00:24:20.563
Hello?

00:24:20.563 --> 00:24:22.146
Yes.

00:24:22.146 --> 00:24:25.426
We'll arrive in about an hour.

00:24:25.426 --> 00:24:29.487
No, I think we should stop by the hotel first.

00:24:29.487 --> 00:24:31.906
And also...

00:24:31.906 --> 00:24:33.387
Sorry?

00:24:38.522 --> 00:24:43.313
This stop is Singyeongju. Singyeongju Station.

00:24:43.313 --> 00:24:46.171
Please make sure to exit
after the train comes to a complete stop.

00:24:46.171 --> 00:24:49.424
Has the schedule been shared
with the Editor as well?

00:24:49.424 --> 00:24:51.384
As far as I know,

00:24:51.384 --> 00:24:54.929
he's on the noon train.

00:24:54.929 --> 00:24:56.665
Okay, then...

00:24:56.665 --> 00:24:59.225
I'll double-check and get back to you.

00:24:59.225 --> 00:25:01.942
- Yes, thank you.
- Doors are opening.

00:25:05.127 --> 00:25:07.192
Hello.

00:25:07.192 --> 00:25:09.653
About tomorrow's event...

00:25:09.653 --> 00:25:10.904
Yes.

00:25:10.904 --> 00:25:13.114
Right.

00:25:13.114 --> 00:25:16.522
I heard briefly, but what kind of video...

00:25:25.835 --> 00:25:27.655
What?

00:25:36.304 --> 00:25:38.700
What is he even doing?

00:25:42.423 --> 00:25:44.562
What was that just now?

00:25:44.562 --> 00:25:45.647
I don't know.

00:25:45.647 --> 00:25:48.230
Where did that come from all of a sudden?

00:25:48.230 --> 00:25:49.387
Guys...

00:25:49.387 --> 00:25:50.897
I have a bad feeling.

00:25:50.897 --> 00:25:52.230
What if...

00:25:52.230 --> 00:25:55.105
it's the Hysterical Cell?

00:25:59.452 --> 00:26:02.470
But the Hysterical Cell is
in the freezer facility.

00:26:02.470 --> 00:26:04.998
What if it woke up

00:26:04.998 --> 00:26:06.730
because of Soon Rok?

00:26:06.730 --> 00:26:08.570
That's it.

00:26:08.570 --> 00:26:12.030
The Hysterical Cell woke up.

00:26:12.030 --> 00:26:13.697
Let's go.

00:26:18.179 --> 00:26:21.355
He just smiled and walked off to take a call.

00:26:21.355 --> 00:26:23.438
What kind of crap is he pulling?

00:26:23.438 --> 00:26:25.395
That won't work on me.

00:26:25.395 --> 00:26:27.630
I'm hearing everything out
before I let this go.

00:26:27.630 --> 00:26:30.846
- Doors are closing.
- What time should I send it by?

00:26:30.846 --> 00:26:32.689
Okay, okay.

00:26:35.238 --> 00:26:37.843
The train is departing.

00:26:46.876 --> 00:26:47.917
Hey!

00:26:47.917 --> 00:26:49.611
I see.

00:26:49.611 --> 00:26:51.421
- If you send the video...
- Hey!

00:26:51.421 --> 00:26:53.779
- I'll review it and decide...
- Hey!

00:26:53.779 --> 00:26:55.800
Yes, thank you.

00:26:55.800 --> 00:26:57.063
Okay, got it.

00:26:57.063 --> 00:26:59.819
- Hey!
- All right.

00:26:59.819 --> 00:27:01.453
Hey!

00:27:06.394 --> 00:27:08.592
Oh, come on...

00:27:08.592 --> 00:27:10.881
Writer Kim!

00:27:10.881 --> 00:27:12.942
Writer...

00:27:12.942 --> 00:27:14.785
Oh no.

00:27:20.995 --> 00:27:22.202
What the...

00:27:22.202 --> 00:27:23.995
Did he just miss the train?

00:27:23.995 --> 00:27:26.875
We're screwed. Totally screwed.

00:27:37.222 --> 00:27:39.149
What the...

00:27:39.149 --> 00:27:41.242
Seriously...

00:27:43.107 --> 00:27:45.092
Did he seriously miss the train?

00:27:45.092 --> 00:27:46.438
Unbelievable.

00:27:46.438 --> 00:27:48.012
Did he do that on purpose?

00:27:48.012 --> 00:27:49.272
Just to avoid talking to her?

00:27:49.272 --> 00:27:50.313
Hey!

00:27:50.313 --> 00:27:53.480
You little bastard...

00:27:58.836 --> 00:28:00.238
I'm so sorry.

00:28:00.238 --> 00:28:02.782
I missed the train while on a call.

00:28:02.782 --> 00:28:05.118
I'll take the next train and catch up.

00:28:05.118 --> 00:28:06.770
I'm really sorry.

00:28:06.770 --> 00:28:08.705
This is insane.

00:28:08.705 --> 00:28:10.248
Okay.

00:28:10.248 --> 00:28:13.551
I'll take your luggage and get off.

00:28:14.711 --> 00:28:16.425
Thank you.

00:28:18.256 --> 00:28:21.732
This guy is seriously unbelievable.

00:28:33.955 --> 00:28:36.465
Fishing Cell!

00:28:36.465 --> 00:28:37.904
You're heading home already?

00:28:37.904 --> 00:28:40.654
Yeah, but I came up empty today.

00:28:40.654 --> 00:28:41.805
Why?

00:28:41.805 --> 00:28:44.874
Yumi was pissed all day.

00:28:45.772 --> 00:28:47.519
You didn't catch a single angry snapper?

00:28:47.519 --> 00:28:50.063
There were tons of them.

00:28:50.063 --> 00:28:53.605
Seriously, so many today.

00:28:58.647 --> 00:29:02.281
Looks like a full haul again!

00:29:25.115 --> 00:29:27.080
Did they just get struck by lightning?

00:29:27.080 --> 00:29:29.063
Yeah, all of a sudden.

00:29:29.063 --> 00:29:30.262
Hold on.

00:29:30.262 --> 00:29:33.333
If all the angry snappers are gone...

00:29:44.907 --> 00:29:48.386
That means Yumi's anger is gone.

00:29:48.386 --> 00:29:51.777
But she was clearly furious.

00:30:16.347 --> 00:30:19.441
The Hysterical Cell should be here...

00:30:20.760 --> 00:30:21.963
No.

00:30:21.963 --> 00:30:24.674
The Hysterical Cell is asleep.

00:30:24.674 --> 00:30:26.342
Then what is it?

00:30:26.342 --> 00:30:27.373
This is weird.

00:30:27.373 --> 00:30:30.638
We've never had lightning like that
in Yumi Village.

00:30:31.563 --> 00:30:32.595
Wait!

00:30:32.595 --> 00:30:34.547
Maybe as Yumi's getting older,

00:30:34.547 --> 00:30:37.451
she's developing some kind of
weird climate changes?

00:30:37.451 --> 00:30:38.918
Like...

00:30:38.918 --> 00:30:41.980
menopause symptoms?

00:30:41.980 --> 00:30:46.188
But there's no way
Yumi's at that stage already.

00:30:49.949 --> 00:30:51.902
What is it?

00:30:52.772 --> 00:30:54.938
Hey!

00:30:56.913 --> 00:30:58.745
What is it?

00:30:58.745 --> 00:31:01.130
Come on, what?

00:31:26.130 --> 00:31:28.029
Power's back on.

00:31:29.534 --> 00:31:31.141
Let's get to work, Soon Rok.

00:31:31.141 --> 00:31:34.174
We've got a ton to do.

00:31:57.901 --> 00:32:00.110
Writer Kim, I'm on the train.

00:32:00.110 --> 00:32:03.263
I'll be there in about 15 minutes.

00:32:04.313 --> 00:32:07.520
I'll be waiting at Platform 9.

00:32:41.772 --> 00:32:44.438
How many minutes left?

00:32:44.438 --> 00:32:45.813
Five minutes.

00:32:45.813 --> 00:32:48.192
- Good.
- Okay.

00:32:48.192 --> 00:32:51.050
Five minutes till that asshole gets here.

00:32:51.050 --> 00:32:53.401
Let's not get dragged into his crap again.

00:32:53.401 --> 00:32:55.672
Smirking, stepping out to take calls...

00:32:55.672 --> 00:32:58.863
If he pulls any more bullshit
and skips the train again...

00:32:58.863 --> 00:33:01.063
we're not letting it slide.

00:33:01.063 --> 00:33:03.217
We crush him.

00:33:03.217 --> 00:33:05.751
We wreck him.

00:33:13.272 --> 00:33:15.027
How much time left?

00:33:15.027 --> 00:33:16.637
One minute.

00:33:16.637 --> 00:33:19.294
He's almost here.

00:33:19.294 --> 00:33:22.417
The train is arriving now.

00:33:24.393 --> 00:33:25.853
Finally!

00:33:25.853 --> 00:33:27.730
We crush him.

00:33:27.730 --> 00:33:30.223
Let's wreck him.

00:33:41.785 --> 00:33:43.996
Where is that bastard?

00:33:43.996 --> 00:33:46.498
I don't see him.

00:33:46.498 --> 00:33:48.250
Did he bail again?

00:33:48.250 --> 00:33:51.219
If he bailed again, I swear...

00:33:56.650 --> 00:33:58.912
- There he is!
- There he is, that bastard!

00:33:58.912 --> 00:34:00.977
That annoying piece of...

00:34:00.977 --> 00:34:03.625
What is it?

00:35:17.228 --> 00:35:19.173
I'm so sorry.

00:35:19.173 --> 00:35:21.425
That was a ridiculous mistake.

00:35:21.425 --> 00:35:23.803
I got off for a second and missed it...

00:35:23.803 --> 00:35:25.763
I'm really sorry.

00:35:25.763 --> 00:35:27.515
Well... Okay.

00:35:27.515 --> 00:35:29.267
They said they'd send a car,

00:35:29.267 --> 00:35:31.477
but it hasn't arrived yet.

00:35:31.477 --> 00:35:34.188
Still, we should have enough time.

00:35:34.188 --> 00:35:35.273
That's a relief.

00:35:35.273 --> 00:35:37.817
We can head over now.

00:35:37.817 --> 00:35:39.860
And...

00:35:39.860 --> 00:35:41.445
about earlier,

00:35:41.445 --> 00:35:44.031
I didn't answer you back then...

00:35:44.031 --> 00:35:46.033
It really was the schedule.

00:35:46.033 --> 00:35:48.286
There's no other reason.

00:35:48.286 --> 00:35:51.433
If I gave you the wrong impression, I'm sorry.

00:35:57.145 --> 00:35:58.963
Look.

00:35:58.963 --> 00:36:01.465
Love Cell is gone.

00:36:01.465 --> 00:36:03.551
Did it wake up?

00:36:03.551 --> 00:36:04.760
Why?

00:36:04.760 --> 00:36:05.928
I don't know.

00:36:05.928 --> 00:36:08.394
Where did it go?

00:36:09.803 --> 00:36:11.267
Wait.

00:36:11.267 --> 00:36:13.900
Then that lightning...

00:36:16.065 --> 00:36:17.866
Let's go.

00:36:36.375 --> 00:36:37.443
Stuff like this...

00:36:37.443 --> 00:36:40.254
only happens in Yumi's novels.

00:36:40.254 --> 00:36:42.222
This is real?

00:36:44.622 --> 00:36:47.178
Can something just hit you like lightning...

00:36:47.178 --> 00:36:49.104
out of nowhere?

00:36:49.897 --> 00:36:53.772
[Episode 9: Drawing the Line
Between Work and Personal Life]

00:36:54.444 --> 00:36:56.230
Alright, now for today's featured work,

00:36:56.230 --> 00:37:00.164
please welcome the writer of
"The Scent of Sincerity," Kim Yumi.

00:37:00.164 --> 00:37:02.964
[Book Talk]

00:37:07.377 --> 00:37:10.938
Hi, hello. I'm writer Kim Yumi.

00:37:10.938 --> 00:37:14.263
Now we'll move on to the Q&A session.

00:37:14.263 --> 00:37:15.956
If anyone has questions for her...

00:37:15.956 --> 00:37:18.876
Honestly, becoming a writer

00:37:18.876 --> 00:37:24.324
was just a vague childhood dream of mine.

00:37:24.324 --> 00:37:26.409
As I got older...

00:37:26.409 --> 00:37:29.387
It was short, but I had a wonderful time.

00:37:29.387 --> 00:37:34.036
I'll be back with another great piece soon.
Thank you.

00:37:35.831 --> 00:37:37.480
I'm a huge fan.

00:37:37.480 --> 00:37:39.855
Oh, thank you.

00:37:40.756 --> 00:37:43.300
Smile.

00:37:44.068 --> 00:37:46.366
- What's your name?
- Jin Hee Jung.

00:37:46.366 --> 00:37:48.340
Jin Hee Jung.

00:37:50.501 --> 00:37:53.288
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

00:38:02.795 --> 00:38:06.026
All her photos turned out great.

00:38:06.026 --> 00:38:09.741
Oh, she even got flowers.

00:38:09.741 --> 00:38:12.945
She's basically a superstar now.

00:38:12.945 --> 00:38:14.854
So pretty.

00:38:14.854 --> 00:38:16.658
Here's your cake.

00:38:16.658 --> 00:38:18.322
Okay.

00:38:20.479 --> 00:38:23.004
- Thank you.
- Bye.

00:38:34.397 --> 00:38:37.888
Writer Kim, I'm here.

00:38:37.888 --> 00:38:39.698
Oh, you're here.

00:38:40.568 --> 00:38:43.320
How was Busan?

00:38:44.161 --> 00:38:46.747
Yeah... it was good.

00:38:46.747 --> 00:38:49.293
I saw photos from your book event online.

00:38:49.293 --> 00:38:51.545
There were a lot of people.

00:38:51.545 --> 00:38:54.305
Yeah, more than I expected.

00:38:54.305 --> 00:38:57.704
You've got tons of fans.

00:38:57.704 --> 00:38:59.195
Not really.

00:38:59.195 --> 00:39:02.505
There were several guest authors.

00:39:02.505 --> 00:39:03.907
But still...

00:39:03.907 --> 00:39:06.876
You seem really calm today.

00:39:08.230 --> 00:39:09.279
Me?

00:39:09.279 --> 00:39:13.066
Yeah, unusually calm.

00:39:13.066 --> 00:39:15.458
Nothing to get worked up about.

00:39:15.458 --> 00:39:17.640
Same as always.

00:39:17.640 --> 00:39:19.160
Yeah?

00:39:23.849 --> 00:39:26.494
Calm, my ass.

00:39:26.494 --> 00:39:28.427
She just doesn't know it yet.

00:39:28.427 --> 00:39:29.605
The whole place

00:39:29.605 --> 00:39:33.022
is in complete chaos right now!

00:39:38.342 --> 00:39:42.220
Just look at the state of things
these past few days.

00:39:42.220 --> 00:39:44.024
Still, she can't show it.

00:39:44.024 --> 00:39:47.535
If she looks calm, that's a win.

00:39:48.389 --> 00:39:50.889
Should we go to the hospital?

00:39:52.949 --> 00:39:54.417
After that lightning strike,

00:39:54.417 --> 00:39:57.820
she's showing signs of partial memory loss.

00:39:57.820 --> 00:40:00.938
"Partial memory loss?"

00:40:00.938 --> 00:40:04.155
When he took off his glasses
and let his hair down...

00:40:04.155 --> 00:40:07.730
he looked like a puppy.

00:40:07.730 --> 00:40:11.852
And when he smiled...

00:40:11.852 --> 00:40:13.503
So cute.

00:40:13.503 --> 00:40:16.147
- Right, totally.
- Right.

00:40:16.147 --> 00:40:17.209
Huh?

00:40:17.209 --> 00:40:20.541
Weren't you all furious at Soon Rok?

00:40:20.541 --> 00:40:22.322
Don't you remember?

00:40:23.654 --> 00:40:24.812
Were we?

00:40:24.812 --> 00:40:26.950
Wait, yeah... I think we were mad.

00:40:26.950 --> 00:40:30.141
But why were we mad again?

00:40:30.141 --> 00:40:32.312
Because

00:40:32.312 --> 00:40:35.272
he said he was leaving?

00:40:35.272 --> 00:40:37.160
- Oh... right.
- Oh... right.

00:40:37.160 --> 00:40:40.003
- That must be it.
- That must be it.

00:40:44.772 --> 00:40:47.855
Love Cell is gone.

00:40:49.298 --> 00:40:51.850
And Naughty Cell...

00:40:52.484 --> 00:40:54.902
The guy scouts...

00:40:54.902 --> 00:40:57.669
Tongue Cell is gone too.

00:40:58.386 --> 00:41:00.147
Why are Naughty Cell and Tongue Cell awake?

00:41:00.147 --> 00:41:02.050
She doesn't even have a boyfriend.

00:41:02.050 --> 00:41:03.813
What are they even going to do?

00:41:03.813 --> 00:41:05.974
They've got nothing to do anyway!

00:41:05.974 --> 00:41:07.897
That lightning just triggered them.

00:41:07.897 --> 00:41:11.104
They didn't wake up for a reason.

00:41:11.104 --> 00:41:12.772
Find them. All of them.

00:41:12.772 --> 00:41:14.813
Before they cause trouble again!

00:41:14.813 --> 00:41:16.605
Without them, I was...

00:41:16.605 --> 00:41:20.938
I mean, Yumi was perfectly fine.

00:41:23.854 --> 00:41:25.673
It's just a glitch from the lightning.

00:41:25.673 --> 00:41:27.431
Nothing serious.

00:41:27.431 --> 00:41:29.563
Everything will go back to normal soon.

00:41:29.563 --> 00:41:32.114
She won't even see Soon Rok again anyway.

00:41:32.114 --> 00:41:34.380
Right.

00:41:35.730 --> 00:41:39.772
Give it a few days,
and it'll be like nothing ever happened.

00:41:46.169 --> 00:41:47.780
Let's start the meeting.

00:41:48.899 --> 00:41:50.613
What's this? A cake?

00:41:50.613 --> 00:41:52.277
Yes, it's a birthday cake.

00:41:52.277 --> 00:41:53.553
A birthday cake?

00:41:53.553 --> 00:41:57.624
I didn't know, but today's PD Shin's birthday.

00:41:57.624 --> 00:42:01.388
I set up a messenger alert,
and it popped up this morning.

00:42:01.388 --> 00:42:04.358
Since we had a meeting today, perfect timing.

00:42:05.289 --> 00:42:06.313
Isn't it pretty?

00:42:06.313 --> 00:42:08.658
It's a low-sugar cake.

00:42:08.658 --> 00:42:10.712
I guess I didn't tell you.

00:42:10.712 --> 00:42:13.042
He's not coming today.

00:42:13.042 --> 00:42:14.736
- Why not?
- Starting today,

00:42:14.736 --> 00:42:16.671
he's off our team.

00:42:16.671 --> 00:42:18.923
- What?
- Last week was his last.

00:42:18.923 --> 00:42:20.842
I forgot to tell you.

00:42:20.842 --> 00:42:22.552
Why?

00:42:22.552 --> 00:42:25.763
He's handling too many teams.
His schedule got messy.

00:42:25.763 --> 00:42:29.100
Let's just eat the cake ourselves.
It looks good.

00:42:29.100 --> 00:42:32.562
I'm so bummed. Seriously bummed.

00:42:32.562 --> 00:42:34.981
Come on, that's a bit much.

00:42:34.981 --> 00:42:36.816
I liked PD Shin.

00:42:36.816 --> 00:42:39.902
Did you come to this meeting
for personal reasons?

00:42:39.902 --> 00:42:41.772
Aren't we doing a farewell?

00:42:41.772 --> 00:42:43.181
At least let's have a team dinner.

00:42:43.181 --> 00:42:46.184
A farewell? We barely even worked together.

00:42:46.184 --> 00:42:47.869
But it's his birthday.

00:42:47.869 --> 00:42:50.288
Let's do a farewell slash birthday party.

00:42:50.288 --> 00:42:53.232
He's not coming here anymore.

00:42:55.480 --> 00:42:58.921
If you're that disappointed,
celebrate with him on your own.

00:42:58.921 --> 00:43:01.630
Okay, I will.

00:43:07.055 --> 00:43:09.015
I sent him a message.

00:43:09.015 --> 00:43:10.600
Saying happy birthday?

00:43:10.600 --> 00:43:14.479
I said I'm really sad he left so suddenly.

00:43:14.479 --> 00:43:17.757
I had no idea you liked him that much.

00:43:17.757 --> 00:43:19.630
He was low-key cute.

00:43:19.630 --> 00:43:24.061
Especially without his glasses,
he looked like a puppy.

00:43:24.061 --> 00:43:27.599
He took them off once...

00:43:28.284 --> 00:43:30.453
and he was seriously adorable.

00:43:30.453 --> 00:43:33.356
So I told him not to wear glasses,
try contacts instead.

00:43:33.356 --> 00:43:35.976
And you know what he said?

00:43:37.251 --> 00:43:39.489
What?

00:43:41.647 --> 00:43:44.384
I wear them to look cold.

00:43:44.384 --> 00:43:46.469
What does that even mean?

00:43:46.469 --> 00:43:49.078
He wants to seem distant

00:43:49.078 --> 00:43:51.980
so people won't bother him.

00:43:51.980 --> 00:43:53.959
That's cute and funny at the same time, right?

00:43:53.959 --> 00:43:55.719
[PD Shin Soon Rok]

00:43:55.719 --> 00:43:58.462
It's PD Shin.

00:43:58.462 --> 00:44:00.280
Oh, Hello?

00:44:00.280 --> 00:44:02.628
Hi.

00:44:02.628 --> 00:44:07.240
Yeah, I'm at the meeting right now.
I heard from Writer Kim.

00:44:07.240 --> 00:44:09.475
Yes, at her studio.

00:44:09.475 --> 00:44:11.188
Really?

00:44:11.188 --> 00:44:13.479
Okay, got it.

00:44:13.479 --> 00:44:15.506
Okay.

00:44:17.629 --> 00:44:20.651
He's nearby right now.

00:44:20.651 --> 00:44:21.793
Oh, really?

00:44:21.793 --> 00:44:23.045
He said he might stop by.

00:44:23.045 --> 00:44:24.076
Right now?

00:44:24.076 --> 00:44:25.952
- Here?
- Yes.

00:44:25.952 --> 00:44:29.223
He asked if it's okay to come up,
so I said yes.

00:44:29.223 --> 00:44:33.558
Perfect timing.
We can cut the cake when he gets here.

00:44:33.558 --> 00:44:35.759
Let's surprise him.

00:44:38.188 --> 00:44:39.231
What?

00:44:39.231 --> 00:44:40.716
Things were finally settling down...

00:44:40.716 --> 00:44:43.922
why is he coming back now?

00:44:43.922 --> 00:44:46.055
What's that sound?

00:44:55.147 --> 00:44:56.789
Hey, Thump, Boom!

00:44:56.789 --> 00:44:59.675
Why are you banging the drums?

00:45:02.522 --> 00:45:05.678
Why is the heart racing all of a sudden?

00:45:05.678 --> 00:45:08.301
I'll leave this in the room
and bring it out later.

00:45:08.301 --> 00:45:09.696
Okay.

00:45:20.270 --> 00:45:22.565
What a ridiculous guy.

00:45:22.565 --> 00:45:25.540
He just left on his own,
and he's suddenly showing up again?

00:45:38.003 --> 00:45:39.992
He's here.

00:45:41.692 --> 00:45:42.930
Oh, Writer Kim.

00:45:42.930 --> 00:45:45.516
Can I use it just once?

00:45:45.516 --> 00:45:46.563
Use what?

00:45:46.563 --> 00:45:49.573
Your lip gloss. I forgot to bring mine.

00:45:51.105 --> 00:45:53.412
Aren't you already wearing some?

00:45:56.891 --> 00:45:59.577
My lips keep getting chapped.

00:46:07.777 --> 00:46:10.788
Nice. I like that it has color.

00:46:16.022 --> 00:46:19.412
Why are you putting on lip gloss
all of a sudden?

00:46:19.412 --> 00:46:22.248
I told you already.

00:46:22.248 --> 00:46:25.025
My lips are chapped.

00:46:25.668 --> 00:46:28.087
- Hello.
- Hello.

00:46:28.087 --> 00:46:30.934
PD Shin is here.

00:46:49.859 --> 00:46:50.901
What?

00:46:50.901 --> 00:46:52.236
Why is my heart racing?

00:46:52.236 --> 00:46:53.522
What's wrong...

00:46:53.522 --> 00:46:55.985
What's wrong with it this time?

00:46:59.076 --> 00:47:01.523
Hello, Writer Kim.

00:47:07.585 --> 00:47:09.476
You're here.

00:47:14.008 --> 00:47:15.092
Did you get some rest?

00:47:15.092 --> 00:47:16.327
After Busan?

00:47:16.327 --> 00:47:17.633
Well... yeah.

00:47:17.633 --> 00:47:18.784
But what brings you...

00:47:18.784 --> 00:47:21.015
I had something to take care of nearby.

00:47:21.015 --> 00:47:22.933
I was going to stop by anyway,

00:47:22.933 --> 00:47:25.519
and then Na Hui contacted me.

00:47:25.519 --> 00:47:27.404
I see.

00:47:27.404 --> 00:47:29.977
This is for you.

00:47:29.977 --> 00:47:31.300
What is it?

00:47:31.300 --> 00:47:33.094
The event organizers

00:47:33.094 --> 00:47:35.613
sent over high-res photos
from your book concert.

00:47:35.613 --> 00:47:38.646
So I picked a good one and framed it.

00:47:39.450 --> 00:47:41.751
You look great in it.

00:47:43.913 --> 00:47:47.083
You didn't have to go this far...

00:47:47.083 --> 00:47:48.967
Thank you.

00:47:52.985 --> 00:47:55.758
Happy birthday, PD Shin.

00:47:55.758 --> 00:47:58.177
It's your birthday today, right?

00:47:58.177 --> 00:47:59.328
How did you know...

00:47:59.328 --> 00:48:01.222
I just know these things.

00:48:01.222 --> 00:48:03.265
How did you find out?

00:48:03.265 --> 00:48:05.726
She's quick with stuff like that.

00:48:05.726 --> 00:48:07.461
Okay, let's sing.

00:48:07.461 --> 00:48:08.896
No, that's okay.

00:48:08.896 --> 00:48:10.564
Writer Kim, let's sing.

00:48:10.564 --> 00:48:13.980
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

00:48:13.980 --> 00:48:16.470
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

00:48:16.470 --> 00:48:18.105
Wait.

00:48:18.105 --> 00:48:19.948
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

00:48:19.948 --> 00:48:23.226
Next comes "dear..."

00:48:23.226 --> 00:48:24.438
Should we use this word?

00:48:24.438 --> 00:48:27.122
It's just part of the song, even for enemies.

00:48:27.122 --> 00:48:28.832
What's the problem with that?

00:48:28.832 --> 00:48:30.834
But still...

00:48:30.834 --> 00:48:33.320
To Shin Soon Rok?

00:48:34.338 --> 00:48:37.908
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

00:48:37.908 --> 00:48:39.843
♪ Dear... ♪

00:48:39.843 --> 00:48:42.095
♪ PD Shin ♪

00:48:42.095 --> 00:48:46.642
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

00:48:46.642 --> 00:48:48.957
Did Yumi just blush?

00:48:48.957 --> 00:48:51.229
Why?

00:48:51.229 --> 00:48:52.439
Put it out.

00:48:52.439 --> 00:48:53.765
Okay.

00:48:56.564 --> 00:48:58.111
Congratulations.

00:48:58.111 --> 00:49:00.337
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

00:49:01.044 --> 00:49:03.408
This is a bit overwhelming.

00:49:03.408 --> 00:49:05.118
The cake...

00:49:05.118 --> 00:49:07.245
Please have some before you go.

00:49:07.245 --> 00:49:09.081
Here, have a seat.

00:49:09.081 --> 00:49:11.014
Yeah.

00:49:11.014 --> 00:49:12.584
I'll do it.

00:49:12.584 --> 00:49:14.920
No, I'll bring it. You cut the cake.

00:49:14.920 --> 00:49:16.752
Okay.

00:49:23.261 --> 00:49:25.330
I got the candles right, didn't I?

00:49:25.330 --> 00:49:26.802
Your 30th birthday.

00:49:26.802 --> 00:49:30.587
What? He is only 30?

00:49:30.587 --> 00:49:32.805
No, I'm not 30.

00:49:32.805 --> 00:49:34.016
Right.

00:49:34.016 --> 00:49:36.276
He must be around my age.

00:49:36.276 --> 00:49:37.416
Exactly...

00:49:37.416 --> 00:49:39.333
I'm 29.

00:49:40.449 --> 00:49:41.863
Seriously?

00:49:41.863 --> 00:49:44.438
Then we're only a year apart?

00:49:44.438 --> 00:49:46.029
Yes.

00:49:46.029 --> 00:49:49.793
What? He's in his twenties?

00:49:49.793 --> 00:49:54.000
Then how old is he compared to Yumi?

00:49:54.000 --> 00:49:55.633
One, two...

00:49:55.633 --> 00:49:58.826
Why are you even counting?

00:49:58.826 --> 00:50:00.524
What are you going to do with that?

00:50:00.524 --> 00:50:02.867
It hurts.

00:50:05.746 --> 00:50:07.862
I'm getting coffee.

00:50:07.862 --> 00:50:09.433
Anyone want some?

00:50:09.433 --> 00:50:12.184
Can I have an iced Americano?

00:50:12.184 --> 00:50:13.603
- Of course.
- Thank you.

00:50:13.603 --> 00:50:14.629
I'll get it.

00:50:14.629 --> 00:50:16.448
I'll do it. Want an Americano too?

00:50:16.448 --> 00:50:17.926
Yes, please.

00:50:19.701 --> 00:50:22.438
Did you have seaweed soup today?

00:50:22.438 --> 00:50:23.488
No.

00:50:23.488 --> 00:50:25.948
Why not? Do you live alone?

00:50:25.948 --> 00:50:27.016
Yes.

00:50:27.016 --> 00:50:28.993
I moved out in college.

00:50:28.993 --> 00:50:31.120
He lives alone?

00:50:31.120 --> 00:50:32.271
Then your parents?

00:50:32.271 --> 00:50:34.899
They retired

00:50:34.899 --> 00:50:38.450
and moved to a country house in Yangpyeong.

00:50:38.450 --> 00:50:40.463
Then do you visit every weekend?

00:50:40.463 --> 00:50:41.752
Sometimes.

00:50:41.752 --> 00:50:44.197
I usually just rest at home on weekends.

00:50:44.197 --> 00:50:46.469
So you're a homebody.

00:50:46.469 --> 00:50:49.209
A committed homebody.

00:50:51.140 --> 00:50:53.017
Is he a homebody too?

00:50:53.017 --> 00:50:54.460
Same as me.

00:50:54.460 --> 00:50:56.562
What are you doing for your birthday?

00:50:56.562 --> 00:50:58.010
A date?

00:51:00.493 --> 00:51:03.372
With who?

00:51:03.372 --> 00:51:04.648
Nice question.

00:51:04.648 --> 00:51:08.070
He doesn't have a girlfriend.

00:51:08.070 --> 00:51:10.165
So what?

00:51:14.820 --> 00:51:16.022
Here.

00:51:16.022 --> 00:51:18.182
Thank you.

00:51:19.267 --> 00:51:21.180
I'll enjoy it.

00:51:29.783 --> 00:51:32.392
The coffee's good.

00:51:32.392 --> 00:51:33.991
Nice and smooth, right?

00:51:33.991 --> 00:51:36.342
Yeah, and the cake's good too.

00:51:36.342 --> 00:51:38.247
Thanks.

00:51:38.247 --> 00:51:42.019
I didn't buy it. Na Hui did.

00:51:42.019 --> 00:51:43.574
I bought it.

00:51:43.574 --> 00:51:45.551
The cake's really good.

00:51:45.551 --> 00:51:46.862
By the way,

00:51:46.862 --> 00:51:50.895
I think this is the most
I've ever heard you talk.

00:51:52.188 --> 00:51:54.837
- Yeah?
- You think so too, right?

00:51:54.837 --> 00:51:56.864
Yeah.

00:51:57.565 --> 00:51:59.519
Maybe because I'm not here for work.

00:51:59.519 --> 00:52:01.376
I feel more relaxed.

00:52:01.376 --> 00:52:04.463
So you felt uncomfortable coming here before?

00:52:04.463 --> 00:52:05.714
I just...

00:52:05.714 --> 00:52:08.325
tend to separate work
and personal life too strictly.

00:52:08.325 --> 00:52:12.418
It just happens without me realizing.

00:52:13.063 --> 00:52:14.748
Not the best trait.

00:52:14.748 --> 00:52:17.313
Then come by casually sometime.

00:52:17.313 --> 00:52:18.448
I will.

00:52:18.448 --> 00:52:20.520
So what are you doing tonight?

00:52:20.520 --> 00:52:21.922
Since no date?

00:52:21.922 --> 00:52:23.106
I'm heading to Busan.

00:52:23.106 --> 00:52:24.274
Again?

00:52:24.274 --> 00:52:26.443
We have a publishing workshop.

00:52:26.443 --> 00:52:29.112
Three nights, four days. All the writers too.

00:52:29.112 --> 00:52:30.764
I heard you're not going

00:52:30.764 --> 00:52:33.325
since it overlaps with your Busan trip.

00:52:33.325 --> 00:52:36.161
Yeah, that's right.

00:52:36.161 --> 00:52:38.197
It felt like too much to go again so soon.

00:52:38.197 --> 00:52:41.790
But I ended up having to go anyway.

00:52:43.497 --> 00:52:46.690
That must be tough,
especially on your birthday.

00:52:48.965 --> 00:52:51.355
I should get going now.

00:52:51.355 --> 00:52:54.813
Happy birthday again.

00:52:54.813 --> 00:52:56.721
Thank you.

00:53:04.400 --> 00:53:05.565
Bye.

00:53:05.565 --> 00:53:07.182
Have a good day.

00:53:11.379 --> 00:53:13.531
Why did I say I wasn't going to the workshop?

00:53:13.531 --> 00:53:14.616
Everyone else is going.

00:53:14.616 --> 00:53:15.772
- Hey.
- Yeah?

00:53:15.772 --> 00:53:19.204
I barely have time to write.
I can't waste a whole week in Busan.

00:53:19.204 --> 00:53:21.653
But Soon Rok's going...

00:53:21.653 --> 00:53:23.011
So?

00:53:23.011 --> 00:53:26.086
- Nothing.
- Hey, what's wrong with you too?

00:53:26.086 --> 00:53:28.605
You're the Rational Cell. Get a grip!

00:53:28.605 --> 00:53:31.355
Going to the workshop isn't bad
for work either.

00:53:31.355 --> 00:53:33.428
It is.

00:53:33.428 --> 00:53:35.691
It is!

00:53:35.691 --> 00:53:37.416
Especially now!

00:53:37.416 --> 00:53:39.844
More than ever!

00:53:41.141 --> 00:53:44.560
Let's just focus and write.

00:53:46.732 --> 00:53:49.426
So what if she steps out briefly
to take out the trash...

00:53:49.426 --> 00:53:51.578
and the Maltese disappears?

00:53:51.578 --> 00:53:55.316
It slips out through the open door,
gets on the elevator, and vanishes...

00:53:55.316 --> 00:53:59.016
The male lead finds out
and gets really mad at her...

00:54:01.262 --> 00:54:03.772
That's a good idea too.

00:54:03.772 --> 00:54:06.772
Or what if the Maltese turns out to be sick,

00:54:06.772 --> 00:54:08.670
so she takes it to the vet

00:54:08.670 --> 00:54:11.770
but her phone dies...

00:54:14.861 --> 00:54:16.232
Looking for the Maltese...

00:54:16.232 --> 00:54:18.472
That's...

00:54:18.472 --> 00:54:20.996
good too.

00:54:20.996 --> 00:54:22.752
But Na Hui...

00:54:22.752 --> 00:54:23.892
Yes?

00:54:23.892 --> 00:54:27.146
Should we wrap up early today?

00:54:27.146 --> 00:54:28.314
Sorry?

00:54:28.314 --> 00:54:31.609
I've got something to take care of.

00:54:31.609 --> 00:54:34.261
Let's keep it short today
and continue online tomorrow.

00:54:34.261 --> 00:54:37.489
Your idea is good.
I think we can wrap it up quickly.

00:54:37.489 --> 00:54:39.399
Okay.

00:54:39.399 --> 00:54:41.799
You're an idea bank.

00:54:44.137 --> 00:54:45.539
What's going on?

00:54:45.539 --> 00:54:47.124
What now?

00:54:47.124 --> 00:54:49.985
We've barely been in this meeting!

00:54:49.985 --> 00:54:52.386
Still don't get it?

00:54:56.258 --> 00:54:58.093
You really don't know

00:54:58.093 --> 00:54:59.662
why Yumi's acting like this?

00:54:59.662 --> 00:55:01.940
Oh, Love Cell!

00:55:01.940 --> 00:55:03.859
Where did you go?

00:55:03.859 --> 00:55:05.392
Hey, Love Cell is here!

00:55:05.392 --> 00:55:07.627
- Get her!
- Got it!

00:55:13.105 --> 00:55:15.397
Idiots!

00:55:15.397 --> 00:55:17.054
How can someone in love

00:55:17.054 --> 00:55:19.947
possibly stay calm?

00:55:19.947 --> 00:55:21.438
What are you talking about?

00:55:21.438 --> 00:55:23.744
The world has changed.

00:55:23.744 --> 00:55:25.371
The moment that lightning struck,

00:55:25.371 --> 00:55:27.607
Yumi changed.

00:55:30.918 --> 00:55:33.253
Hello, Writer Kim?

00:55:33.253 --> 00:55:35.130
PD Jang.

00:55:35.130 --> 00:55:36.965
Are you in Busan?

00:55:36.965 --> 00:55:40.498
Yeah, I came down this morning with the editor.

00:55:41.303 --> 00:55:44.123
I'm thinking of coming down too.

00:55:44.123 --> 00:55:46.183
Would there be a place for me to stay?

00:55:46.183 --> 00:55:48.230
Oh, you're coming?

00:55:48.230 --> 00:55:52.647
Yes. It's rare to see all the writers together,

00:55:52.647 --> 00:55:55.358
so I thought I should go.

00:55:55.358 --> 00:55:57.397
Of course, you're more than welcome.

00:55:57.397 --> 00:55:59.445
Come on down.

00:55:59.445 --> 00:56:02.156
I'll take the evening train.

00:56:02.156 --> 00:56:04.841
The editor will be glad to hear that.

00:56:04.841 --> 00:56:06.104
Come down soon.

00:56:06.104 --> 00:56:08.529
I'll call you when I get there.

00:56:08.529 --> 00:56:10.541
Okay.

00:56:12.022 --> 00:56:15.313
I've lost it. I've seriously lost it.

00:56:18.272 --> 00:56:20.382
Now, the Prime Cell position...

00:56:20.382 --> 00:56:22.050
- I'm taking it back.
- What?

00:56:22.050 --> 00:56:25.345
You might as well hand over this place too.

00:56:25.345 --> 00:56:27.014
Are you insane?

00:56:27.014 --> 00:56:29.099
Who do you think you are, taking Prime Cell?

00:56:29.099 --> 00:56:32.335
What are you doing? Get her!

00:57:10.313 --> 00:57:12.768
What the hell are you doing, Kim Yumi?

00:57:12.768 --> 00:57:14.102
Seriously...

00:57:14.102 --> 00:57:18.675
What are you doing? You've completely lost it.

00:57:25.614 --> 00:57:27.366
You've lost it.

00:57:27.366 --> 00:57:29.618
You can't even separate work and personal life.

00:57:29.618 --> 00:57:33.038
And someone out there is
so perfectly professional...

00:57:33.038 --> 00:57:35.538
You've seriously lost it.

00:57:59.398 --> 00:58:02.198
[Seoul]

00:58:04.669 --> 00:58:07.281
God, how old are you, seriously?

00:58:07.281 --> 00:58:09.385
What the hell is wrong with you...

00:58:09.385 --> 00:58:10.993
Sorry?

00:58:10.993 --> 00:58:13.306
Oh, nothing.

00:58:13.960 --> 00:58:16.512
I've seriously lost it.

00:58:25.841 --> 00:58:27.407
Hello, PD Jang.

00:58:27.407 --> 00:58:30.596
You haven't gotten on the train yet, right?

00:58:30.596 --> 00:58:32.737
I just got to the station.

00:58:32.737 --> 00:58:35.017
- I was about to buy a ticket...
- Oh, perfect.

00:58:35.017 --> 00:58:39.105
PD Shin is heading down now.
He's still at the station.

00:58:39.105 --> 00:58:40.188
Sorry?

00:58:40.188 --> 00:58:42.466
You can just come down with him.

00:58:42.466 --> 00:58:45.110
I'll have him buy your ticket.

00:58:45.110 --> 00:58:47.261
Okay.

00:59:01.960 --> 00:59:03.712
This is insane.

00:59:03.712 --> 00:59:07.598
Why am I this nervous?
It's not even a big deal...

00:59:10.552 --> 00:59:12.625
Writer Kim.

00:59:47.972 --> 00:59:52.428
[A one-sided love has begun]

00:59:58.592 --> 00:59:59.605
Fine.

00:59:59.605 --> 01:00:01.819
I'll admit it.

01:00:01.819 --> 01:00:03.939
I...

01:00:03.939 --> 01:00:05.524
like

01:00:05.524 --> 01:00:07.866
Soon Rok.

01:00:12.404 --> 01:00:15.341
You think you can take my place?

01:00:15.341 --> 01:00:17.618
I've built this up for years!

01:00:17.618 --> 01:00:20.919
I'm still the Prime Cell!

01:00:22.980 --> 01:00:24.041
Let's see, then.

01:00:24.041 --> 01:00:27.001
Who ends up winning.

01:00:27.001 --> 01:00:28.447
Ridiculous.

01:00:28.447 --> 01:00:31.522
Shin Soon Rok isn't even interested in Yumi.

01:00:31.522 --> 01:00:33.958
He doesn't even like her.

01:00:33.958 --> 01:00:35.093
She probably scares him.

01:00:35.093 --> 01:00:37.011
After the way she snapped at him.

01:00:37.011 --> 01:00:39.775
He's only dealing with her because it's work.

01:00:39.775 --> 01:00:42.271
Don't you get that?

01:00:50.424 --> 01:00:51.617
Have a seat.

01:00:51.617 --> 01:00:53.130
Okay.

01:01:02.518 --> 01:01:04.718
I thought you said you weren't going earlier.

01:01:04.718 --> 01:01:06.525
Yeah, I did...

01:01:06.525 --> 01:01:08.811
but the meeting wrapped up quickly.

01:01:08.811 --> 01:01:11.880
PD Jang kept insisting I come.

01:01:11.880 --> 01:01:14.033
I see.

01:01:14.033 --> 01:01:15.824
Guess we ended up going together.

01:01:15.824 --> 01:01:17.951
The train is departing.

01:01:17.951 --> 01:01:19.984
Yeah.

01:01:41.760 --> 01:01:43.912
Want me to grab you a coffee?

01:01:43.912 --> 01:01:46.331
I'm good. I already had one.

01:01:46.331 --> 01:01:48.424
Okay.

01:02:41.230 --> 01:02:42.679
See?

01:02:42.679 --> 01:02:45.140
You're really going to go for a hopeless crush?

01:02:45.140 --> 01:02:46.385
I don't care.

01:02:46.385 --> 01:02:47.668
What?

01:02:47.668 --> 01:02:49.727
What matters is...

01:02:49.727 --> 01:02:52.228
I'm awake now.

01:03:05.144 --> 01:03:06.786
What matters is...

01:03:06.786 --> 01:03:08.813
Yumi's dull, lifeless routine

01:03:08.813 --> 01:03:11.391
is finally over.

01:03:58.480 --> 01:03:59.505
It's Soon Rok!

01:03:59.505 --> 01:04:01.563
This is insane, seriously!

01:04:01.563 --> 01:04:03.176
Yumi, get it together!

01:04:03.176 --> 01:04:04.480
This is writer Kim Ju Ho.

01:04:04.480 --> 01:04:06.016
Nice to meet you.

01:04:06.016 --> 01:04:07.480
If you don't mind me asking,
what year were you?

01:04:07.480 --> 01:04:10.533
Wait, wait! Why bring that up out of nowhere?

01:04:10.533 --> 01:04:12.727
You sure Yumi's single?

01:04:12.727 --> 01:04:15.313
Are they trying to
set me up with him or something?

01:04:15.313 --> 01:04:17.398
They actually look pretty good together, huh?

01:04:17.398 --> 01:04:18.925
I don't think so.

01:04:18.925 --> 01:04:19.984
Have some confidence.

01:04:19.984 --> 01:04:21.569
Let's make this a thing.

01:04:21.569 --> 01:04:24.853
- Let's make this a thing!
- Let's make this a thing!